A **hydration error in Next.js** happens when **the HTML generated on the server does not match the HTML that React generates on the client during hydration**.

Think of hydration as **React “waking up” server‑rendered HTML and attaching event handlers to it**.  
If React sees **even a small mismatch**, it throws a hydration error.

***

# ✅ What EXACTLY Causes a Hydration Error?

## 🔑 Core Rule (This is the root cause)

> **Server-rendered HTML ≠ Client-rendered HTML on first render**

Anything that breaks this equality causes hydration to fail.

***

# 🧠 What Is Hydration (Quick Context)

    Server → HTML (SSR / SSG)
    Browser loads HTML
    ↓
    React hydrates (attaches JS + events)

✅ Hydration assumes **HTML is identical** on both sides  
❌ If not → hydration error

***

# 🔥 Most Common Causes of Hydration Errors (With Examples)

***

## 1️⃣ Using Browser‑Only APIs During Render

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
function Page() {
  return <div>{window.innerWidth}</div>;
}
```

### ❌ Why It Breaks

*   Server: `window` does NOT exist
*   Client: `window.innerWidth` exists

➡️ Server HTML ≠ Client HTML

✅ **Hydration error**

***

### ✅ Fix

```jsx
function Page() {
  const [width, setWidth] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    setWidth(window.innerWidth);
  }, []);

  return <div>{width}</div>;
}
```

✅ Browser‑only code runs **after hydration**

***

## 2️⃣ Non‑Deterministic Values (`Date`, `Math.random`)

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
<div>{new Date().toLocaleString()}</div>
```

### ❌ Why

*   Server time ≠ Client time
*   Even milliseconds difference breaks HTML

***

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
<div>{Math.random()}</div>
```

Server:

    0.38294

Client:

    0.91247

💥 Hydration error

***

### ✅ Fix

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  setTime(new Date().toLocaleString());
}, []);
```

***

## 3️⃣ Conditional Rendering Based on `window` / `document`

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
{typeof window !== "undefined" && <Component />}
```

### Why It Breaks

*   Server: condition is `false`
*   Client: condition is `true`

HTML mismatch ❌

***

### ✅ Fix

Use client‑only rendering:

```jsx
const [mounted, setMounted] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => setMounted(true), []);

if (!mounted) return null;
```

***

## 4️⃣ Incorrect HTML Structure (Invalid DOM)

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
<p>
  <div>Text</div>
</p>
```

### Why

*   Browser auto‑fixes invalid HTML
*   React expects exact match
*   DOM tree differs

💥 Hydration error

***

### ✅ Fix

```jsx
<div>
  <p>Text</p>
</div>
```

***

## 5️⃣ Different Data Between SSR and Client

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
const items = getItems(); // changes every request
```

Server fetch returns:

    [1, 2, 3]

Client fetch returns:

    [1, 2, 3, 4]

Mismatch → hydration error

***

### ✅ Fix

*   Use `getServerSideProps`
*   Pass stable props
*   Re‑fetch inside `useEffect` if needed

***

## 6️⃣ CSS‑in‑JS Mismatch (Styled‑Components / Emotion)

### ❌ Problem

*   Styles generated differently
*   Class names differ between server & client

💥 Hydration error

***

### ✅ Fix

Ensure proper SSR setup:

*   `styled-components` Babel plugin
*   Correct Emotion cache setup

***

## 7️⃣ Using `useLayoutEffect` on Server

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
useLayoutEffect(() => {
  // runs only on client
}, []);
```

### Why

*   Server skips it
*   Client runs it before paint
*   HTML mismatch

***

### ✅ Fix

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  // safe
}, []);
```

***

## 8️⃣ Locale / Language Differences

### ❌ Problem

```jsx
{number.toLocaleString()}
```

*   Server locale ≠ Client locale

➡️ Output mismatch

***

### ✅ Fix

Specify locale explicitly:

```js
number.toLocaleString("en-US");
```

