# 🧠 Why React Can’t “Fix It”

You might ask:

> “Why doesn’t React just update it?”

Because hydration is **not normal rendering**.

*   React assumes DOM is correct
*   Fixing it would:
    *   Lose server performance benefits
    *   Break streaming / concurrency
    *   Cause flicker

So React **fails fast instead**.

***

# ✅ Golden Rule (Precise, Not Vague)

> A hydration error occurs when **any difference exists between the server‑generated DOM and the client’s first render output — including text, structure, or attributes**.

